  "texts": [
    "Note that |p ′ | ≤ 2|p|+1.",
    "Thus, using (4.3), we obtain",
    "for all x ∈ H, µ ∈ P 2 (µ), and p ∈ H. Now, we consider the function Ψ: R → R, Ψ(θ):= H(x, µ, p ′ + θ(p -p ′)).",
    "Since H is concave in its last varaible, Ψ is also concave.",
    "Thus, Ψ is Lipschitz continuous on [0, 1], hence differentiable almost everywhere."
  ],
